Handles a HttpHeaderRequest from a user or extType.

Parameters values same as in handleHttpHeaderRequest with ParserExternalAuthHttpSettings.

int ParserExternalAuth::handleHttpHeaderRequest (  const handleHttpHeaderRequestParam &  p,
int &  status,
UserItem *&  setUserItem
) 
 

Handles a HttpHeaderRequest authentication.

Parameters:
ireq The request to authenticate.
peh The settings.
clientType The client identfier.
clientTypeOptions The client identfier options.
licenceKeys The licence keys of the client, empty if none.
programV The program version of the client, NULL if none.
activationCode The activation code used, empty if none.
status Set to the status of the reply. -1 is NOT_OK. -2 is TIMEOUT. -3 is EXPIRED. -4 is UNAUTHORIZED.
setUserItem Set to a newed UserItem of the authenticated user.
clientUserID The user-id from the client.
currentID The current (hardware) id of the client.
newID The next (hardware) id of the client. May be same as currentID.
clientUser The user the client think it has, if any.
